claim: Vaccination with a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine may induce a more robust antibody response than egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
explanation: First page of Flublok prescribing information showing indications, dosage and administration (0.5 mL intramuscular), dosage forms and strengths, contraindications, warnings and precautions, adverse reactions, use in specific populations, and a table of contents for the full prescribing information. does not support the claim — the image contains only labeling and table of contents without any clinical or immunogenicity data comparing a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine to egg-based standard-dose vaccines. Note: Analysis limited by the image showing only administrative and structural information; no efficacy or antibody response data are present.
